{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775904488957,"sessionID":"ses_283da1765ffedhoSCLBiDKTtz5","part":{"id":"prt_d7c2676d90019OLmF6L8VU2tXP","messageID":"msg_d7c263811001MkNVLn6NfebI60","sessionID":"ses_283da1765ffedhoSCLBiDKTtz5","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-028 Delta Specification: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document specifies the delta changes required to implement the AgentRuntimeClient SDK for Python.\n\n## New Components\n\n### 1. AgentRuntimeClient Class\n\n**Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/runtime_client.py`\n\n**Description:** Main client class for interacting with the AgentRuntime service.\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `create_agent(config: AgentConfig) -> Agent`\n- `start_agent(agent_id: str) -> AgentStatus`\n- `stop_agent(agent_id: str) -> AgentStatus`\n- `delete_agent(agent_id: str) -> None`\n- `get_agent(agent_id: str) -> Agent`\n- `list_agents(filters: AgentFilter) -> List[Agent]`\n- `stream_events(agent_id: str) -> Iterator[AgentEvent]`\n\n### 2. Configuration Models\n\n**Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/models/config.py`\n\n**Description:** Pydantic models for agent configuration.\n\n**Classes:**\n- `AgentConfig`\n- `AgentResources`\n- `AgentEnvironment`\n\n### 3. Response Models\n\n**Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/models/responses.py`\n\n**Description:** Pydantic models for API responses.\n\n**Classes:**\n- `Agent`\n- `AgentStatus`\n- `AgentEvent`\n- `AgentFilter`\n\n### 4. Exception Hierarchy\n\n**Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/exceptions.py`\n\n**Description:** Custom exceptions for error handling.\n\n**Classes:**\n- `AgentRuntimeError` (base)\n- `AgentNotFoundError`\n- `AgentCreationError`\n- `ConnectionError`\n- `AuthenticationError`\n\n### 5. Retry Logic\n\n**Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/retry.py`\n\n**Description:** Retry decorator and utilities.\n\n## Modified Components\n\nNone - this is a new feature implementation.\n\n## Interface Contracts\n\n### gRPC/HTTP Endpoints\n\nThe client will communicate with the following endpoints:\n\n- `POST /v1/agents` - Create agent\n- `GET /v1/agents/{id}` - Get agent\n- `DELETE /v1/agents/{id}` - Delete agent\n- `POST /v1/agents/{id}/start` - Start agent\n- `POST /v1/agents/{id}/stop` - Stop agent\n- `GET /v1/agents` - List agents\n- `GET /v1/agents/{id}/events` - Stream events\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `httpx` or `aiohttp` for HTTP client\n- `pydantic` for data validation\n- `tenacity` for retry logic\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-025/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775904488927,"end":1775904488955}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775904488958,"sessionID":"ses_283da1765ffedhoSCLBiDKTtz5","part":{"id":"prt_d7c26b5cf001dahW4BQ65M342O","messageID":"msg_d7c263811001MkNVLn6NfebI60","sessionID":"ses_283da1765ffedhoSCLBiDKTtz5","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/design.md","content":"# AR-028 Design: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    AgentRuntimeClient                        │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐       │\n│  │ Sync Client  │  │ Async Client │  │  Streaming   │       │\n│  └──────┬───────┘  └──────┬───────┘  └──────┬───────┘       │\n│         └──────────────────┴──────────────────┘              │\n│                            │                                 │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────┐       │\n│  │              Transport Layer (HTTP/gRPC)           │       │\n│  │  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐   │       │\n│  │  │  Request   │  │   Retry    │  │  Circuit   │   │       │\n│  │  │  Builder   │  │   Logic    │  │  Breaker   │   │       │\n│  │  └────────────┘  └────────────┘  └────────────┘   │       │\n│  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘       │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n                              ▼\n                    ┌─────────────────────┐\n                    │   AgentRuntime API  │\n                    └─────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Design Principles\n\n1. **Pythonic API**: Follow Python conventions and best practices\n2. **Type Safety**: Full type hints and Pydantic validation\n3. **Async-First**: Support both sync and async patterns\n4. **Fail-Fast**: Clear exceptions with actionable error messages\n5. **Observability**: Built-in logging and event streaming\n\n## Class Design\n\n### AgentRuntimeClient\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    \"\"\"Client for interacting with the AgentRuntime service.\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        base_url: str,\n        api_key: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: float = 30.0,\n        max_retries: int = 3\n    ):\n        ...\n    \n    def create_agent(self, config: AgentConfig) -> Agent:\n        \"\"\"Create a new agent.\"\"\"\n        ...\n    \n    async def acreate_agent(self, config: AgentConfig) -> Agent:\n        \"\"\"Async create a new agent.\"\"\"\n        ...\n```\n\n### Error Handling Strategy\n\n- Custom exception hierarchy for different error types\n- Automatic retry with exponential backoff for transient errors\n- Circuit breaker pattern for cascading failure prevention\n\n## Data Flow\n\n1. User calls client method with Pydantic model parameters\n2. Request is serialized and validated\n3. Transport layer sends request with retry logic\n4. Response is deserialized into Pydantic models\n5. Result or exception is returned to user\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-025/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/design.md","time":{"start":1775904488931,"end":1775904488957}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775904488961,"sessionID":"ses_283da1765ffedhoSCLBiDKTtz5","part":{"id":"prt_d7c26f7f6001XQLjPqpBUtmkTk","messageID":"msg_d7c263811001MkNVLn6NfebI60","sessionID":"ses_283da1765ffedhoSCLBiDKTtz5","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/plan.md","content":"# AR-028 Implementation Plan: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Phase 1: Foundation (Day 1)\n\n### Tasks\n1. **Setup project structure**\n   - Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/` directory\n   - Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/models/` directory\n   - Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/exceptions.py`\n\n2. **Define data models**\n   - Implement `AgentConfig` model\n   - Implement `Agent` response model\n   - Implement `AgentStatus` model\n   - Implement `AgentEvent` model\n   - Implement `AgentFilter` model\n\n3. **Implement exception hierarchy**\n   - Create base `AgentRuntimeError`\n   - Create specific exception classes\n\n## Phase 2: Core Client (Day 1-2)\n\n### Tasks\n1. **Implement base client**\n   - Create `BaseClient` with common functionality\n   - Implement request/response handling\n   - Add logging infrastructure\n\n2. **Implement sync client**\n   - Create `AgentRuntimeClient` class\n   - Implement `create_agent()` method\n   - Implement `get_agent()` method\n   - Implement `list_agents()` method\n   - Implement `start_agent()` method\n   - Implement `stop_agent()` method\n   - Implement `delete_agent()` method\n\n3. **Implement retry logic**\n   - Integrate tenacity for retry handling\n   - Configure exponential backoff\n   - Define retryable vs non-retryable errors\n\n## Phase 3: Async Support (Day 2)\n\n### Tasks\n1. **Implement async client**\n   - Create `AsyncAgentRuntimeClient` class\n   - Implement all async variants of sync methods\n   - Ensure proper session management\n\n2. **Implement event streaming**\n   - Create streaming endpoint support\n   - Implement `stream_events()` method\n   - Handle connection lifecycle\n\n## Phase 4: Testing & Documentation (Day 3)\n\n### Tasks\n1. **Unit tests**\n   - Test all client methods\n   - Test retry logic\n   - Test error handling\n   - Mock transport layer\n\n2. **Integration tests**\n   - Test against mock server\n   - Verify serialization/deserialization\n   - Test streaming functionality\n\n3. **Documentation**\n   - Add docstrings to all public APIs\n   - Create usage examples\n   - Write README section\n\n## Dependencies\n\n```\nsdk-python/\n├── src/agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py\n│   ├── client/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── runtime_client.py\n│   │   ├── async_client.py\n│   │   └── retry.py\n│   ├── models/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── config.py\n│   │   └── responses.py\n│   └── exceptions.py\n```\n\n## Risk Mitigation\n\n- Use established libraries (httpx, pydantic, tenacity)\n- Follow existing project patterns from other SDKs\n- Regular testing during development\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-025/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/plan.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/plan.md","time":{"start":1775904488933,"end":1775904488959}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775904488962,"sessionID":"ses_283da1765ffedhoSCLBiDKTtz5","part":{"id":"prt_d7c273969001Ni4V0IdWTod5zN","messageID":"msg_d7c263811001MkNVLn6NfebI60","sessionID":"ses_283da1765ffedhoSCLBiDKTtz5","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/tests.md","content":"# AR-028 Test Specification: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Test Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### 1. Model Validation Tests\n- Test `AgentConfig` validation\n  - Valid configurations pass\n  - Invalid configurations raise ValidationError\n  - Default values applied correctly\n\n- Test response model parsing\n  - Parse valid JSON responses\n  - Handle missing optional fields\n  - Handle malformed responses\n\n#### 2. Client Method Tests\n- Test `create_agent()`\n  - Success case returns Agent\n  - Server error raises appropriate exception\n  - Network error triggers retry\n  - Invalid config raises ValidationError\n\n- Test `get_agent()`\n  - Success case returns Agent\n  - Not found raises AgentNotFoundError\n  - Parse error raises ResponseError\n\n- Test `list_agents()`\n  - Success case returns List[Agent]\n  - Filters applied correctly\n  - Pagination handled properly\n\n- Test `start_agent()` / `stop_agent()`\n  - Success updates status\n  - Invalid state transitions handled\n  - Errors propagated correctly\n\n- Test `delete_agent()`\n  - Success returns None\n  - Not found handled appropriately\n\n#### 3. Retry Logic Tests\n- Test exponential backoff\n- Test max retry limit\n- Test non-retryable errors\n- Test circuit breaker\n\n#### 4. Async Client Tests\n- Test all sync methods have async equivalents\n- Test concurrent requests\n- Test async context manager\n\n#### 5. Event Streaming Tests\n- Test event parsing\n- Test connection errors\n- Test reconnection logic\n- Test proper cleanup\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n#### 1. Mock Server Tests\n- Start mock server\n- Test full CRUD flow\n- Test error scenarios\n\n#### 2. End-to-End Tests\n- Test against real (staging) API if available\n- Verify authentication flow\n- Test rate limiting behavior\n\n## Test Coverage Goals\n\n- Overall coverage: >= 80%\n- Client methods: 100%\n- Model validation: 100%\n- Error handling: 100%\n\n## Test Files Structure\n\n```\nsdk-python/tests/\n├── unit/\n│   ├── test_models.py\n│   ├── test_client.py\n│   ├── test_async_client.py\n│   ├── test_retry.py\n│   └── test_exceptions.py\n├── integration/\n│   ├── test_client_integration.py\n│   └── conftest.py\n└── fixtures/\n    ├── agent_config.json\n    └── agent_response.json\n```\n\n## Key Test Cases\n\n### TC001: Create Agent Success\n```python\nclient = AgentRuntimeClient(base_url=\"http://localhost:8080\")\nconfig = AgentConfig(name=\"test-agent\", image=\"python:3.9\")\nagent = client.create_agent(config)\nassert agent.id is not None\nassert agent.name == \"test-agent\"\nassert agent.status == AgentStatus.CREATED\n```\n\n### TC002: Create Agent Validation Error\n```python\nclient = AgentRuntimeClient(base_url=\"http://localhost:8080\")\nconfig = AgentConfig(name=\"\", image=\"python:3.9\")  # Invalid: empty name\nwith pytest.raises(ValidationError):\n    client.create_agent(config)\n```\n\n### TC003: Get Agent Not Found\n```python\nclient = AgentRuntimeClient(base_url=\"http://localhost:8080\")\nwith pytest.raises(AgentNotFoundError):\n    client.get_agent(\"non-existent-id\")\n```\n\n### TC004: Retry on Network Error\n```python\n# Mock transport to fail twice then succeed\nclient = AgentRuntimeClient(base_url=\"http://localhost:8080\", max_retries=3)\nagent = client.get_agent(\"test-id\")  # Should retry and succeed\n```\n\n### TC005: Async Client Flow\n```python\nasync def test_async_create():\n    client = AsyncAgentRuntimeClient(base_url=\"http://localhost:8080\")\n    config = AgentConfig(name=\"test-agent\", image=\"python:3.9\")\n    agent = await client.create_agent(config)\n    assert agent.id is not None\n```\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-025/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/tests.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/tests.md","time":{"start":1775904488936,"end":1775904488961}}}}
