{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775904488965,"sessionID":"ses_283da1765ffedhoSCLBiDKTtz5","part":{"id":"prt_d7c27e236001J6tz701jbjtYs0","messageID":"msg_d7c263811001MkNVLn6NfebI60","sessionID":"ses_283da1765ffedhoSCLBiDKTtz5","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/notes.md","content":"# AR-028 Notes: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Created\nDate: 2026-04-11\n\n## Context\n\nThis change implements the Python SDK client for the AgentRuntime service. The client will provide both synchronous and asynchronous APIs for managing agent lifecycle, configuration, and monitoring.\n\n## Design Decisions\n\n### HTTP vs gRPC\nInitially considering HTTP/REST for broader compatibility, but gRPC may be evaluated if performance becomes critical.\n\n### Library Choices\n- **HTTP Client**: `httpx` - supports both sync and async, modern API\n- **Validation**: `pydantic` - already used in project, excellent type support\n- **Retry**: `tenacity` - battle-tested, flexible retry strategies\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. What is the exact API endpoint structure for the AgentRuntime service?\n2. Are there existing API specifications (OpenAPI/Swagger) to reference?\n3. What authentication mechanism should the client support?\n4. Should we support connection pooling for high-throughput scenarios?\n\n## References\n\n- Project: agentcube\n- Module: sdk-python\n- Language: Python 3.9+\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-025/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/notes.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/notes.md","time":{"start":1775904488942,"end":1775904488965}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775904489331,"sessionID":"ses_283da1765ffedhoSCLBiDKTtz5","part":{"id":"prt_d7c264613001K3PPZhJ4xlNJOk","messageID":"msg_d7c263811001MkNVLn6NfebI60","sessionID":"ses_283da1765ffedhoSCLBiDKTtz5","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/spec.yaml","content":"id: AR-028\ntitle: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\nmodule: sdk-python\nlanguage: Python\nsize: M\nstatus: open\n\n# AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n# Module: sdk-python\n# Language: Python\n# Size: M\n\n# OpenSpec Metadata\nopenspec:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  project: agentcube\n\n# Architecture Requirement\nrequirement:\n  type: client-sdk\n  description: |\n    Implement an AgentRuntimeClient class within the sdk-python module to provide\n    a Python SDK for interacting with the AgentRuntime service. This client will\n    enable developers to programmatically create, manage, and monitor agents\n    through a clean, Pythonic API that abstracts the underlying gRPC/HTTP\n    communication with the AgentRuntime.\n\n# Scope\nscope:\n  in:\n    - AgentRuntimeClient class implementation\n    - Agent lifecycle management (create, start, stop, delete)\n    - Agent configuration and deployment APIs\n    - Event streaming and monitoring capabilities\n    - Error handling and retry logic\n    - Async/sync API support\n    - Type hints and pydantic models for all API objects\n  out:\n    - CLI tool for agent management (separate AR)\n    - Authentication/authorization implementation (assumes existing)\n    - WebSocket-based real-time updates (separate AR)\n    - Multi-region failover handling (separate AR)\n\n# Acceptance Criteria\nacceptance:\n  - AgentRuntimeClient provides clean, Pythonic API for all runtime operations\n  - Both synchronous and asynchronous APIs are supported\n  - Comprehensive type hints for IDE support and type checking\n  - Proper error handling with custom exception hierarchy\n  - Retry logic with exponential backoff for transient failures\n  - Event streaming supports real-time agent status updates\n  - Unit and integration test coverage >= 80%\n  - Documentation with usage examples\n\n# References\nreferences:\n  - https://docs.pydantic.dev/\n  - https://grpc.io/docs/languages/python/\n  - https://www.python-httpx.org/\n\n# Estimation\nestimation:\n  size: M\n  story_points: 5\n  days: 3\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-025/spec.yaml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/spec.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/spec.yaml","time":{"start":1775904488922,"end":1775904489328}}}}
